Plug-in name: Obfuscator
Plug-in shortname: obfuscator
Description: obfuscator for confidential code

Most options of the form '-obfuscator-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-obfuscator-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-obfuscate          print an obfuscated version of the input files and
                    exit.
                    Disable any other Frama-C analysis. (opposite option is
                    -no-obfuscate)
-obfuscator-dictionary <f>  generate the dictionary into file <f> (on stdout
                    by default) (preferably use -obfuscator-dictionary="f")
-obfuscator-string-dictionary <f>  generate the dictionary of literal strings
                    into file <f> (in the same place than the code by
                    default) (preferably use
                    -obfuscator-string-dictionary="f")

*** DEBUG

-obfuscator-debug <n>  level of debug for plug-in Obfuscator (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-obfuscator-help    help of plug-in Obfuscator
-obfuscator-h       alias for option -obfuscator-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-obfuscator-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Obfuscator to a
                    file. <K> is a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -obfuscator-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-obfuscator-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -obfuscator-msg-key help to get a list
                    of available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -obfuscator-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-obfuscator-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in Obfuscator (default
                    to 1)
-obfuscator-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category
                    <k1> to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -obfuscator-warn-key
                    help to get a list of available categories, and * to
                    enable all categories. Possible statuses are inactive,
                    feedback, warning, error, abort, feedback-once,
                    warning-once, error-once. Defaults to warning.
                    (preferably use
                    -obfuscator-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
